<s> Just a quick note to agree with Jessica Chaiken, working as a British Sign Language (BSL) interpreter, variation of Sign Language occurs within the UK, as well as internationally.  </s>
<s> With regard to;  </s>
<s> This 'signed english' does not represent BSL but rather a signed language in its own right, probably a signed system called Makaton.  </s>
<s> Lastly, within the UK there is also Signed Supported English (SSE) which varies from the phonology, morphology, and syntax in BSL.  </s>
<s> This may seem off topic but the understanding of the difference phonology etc, in Signed Languages is important for Deaf people's access to information.  </s>
